WEBVTT

1
00:00:11.386 --> 00:00:13.857
Excuse me. Can I get a comment. please?

2
00:00:19.334 --> 00:00:20.359
Yes. ma'am.

3
00:00:20.536 --> 00:00:22.369
We're just gonna keep you
right back here.

4
00:00:27.648 --> 00:00:29.983
- Captain.
- Agent Lisbon.

5
00:00:30.152 --> 00:00:31.917
Don't think we'll be needing you guys.

6
00:00:32.089 --> 00:00:34.083
We like the neighbor kid
who found the body.

7
00:00:34.260 --> 00:00:37.255
- Did he confess?
- Eh. he's a real squirrel. Hard to say...

8
00:00:37.431 --> 00:00:39.753
- Did you kill her?
- Did you kill her?

9
00:00:45.913 --> 00:00:49.216
Mercy's father
would like to give a brief statement.

10
00:00:49.386 --> 00:00:52.790
I just wanna take a moment
and thank everyone in law enforcement...

11
00:00:52.958 --> 00:00:57.332
and all the volunteers who helped us
in the search for our beloved daughter.

12
00:01:00.138 --> 00:01:03.941
The way that this entire community
has come together to support me...

13
00:01:04.845 --> 00:01:09.115
and Juniper in this terrible time
has been of great comfort to us.

14
00:01:12.960 --> 00:01:15.761
And now I would just like to ask that...

15
00:01:15.931 --> 00:01:22.638
you give us some time. space and privacy
to grieve for our daughter. Thank you.

16
00:02:40.611 --> 00:02:41.636
Hello. Mrs. Tolliver.

17
00:02:43.182 --> 00:02:46.677
- Who are you?
- My name's Patrick Jane.

18
00:02:47.389 --> 00:02:48.858
I'm here to help you.

19
00:02:50.394 --> 00:02:51.795
Would you like a cup of tea?

20
00:02:54.769 --> 00:02:56.763
Yes. I would. Thank you.

21
00:02:59.711 --> 00:03:01.010
You must be tired.

22
00:03:02.849 --> 00:03:04.648
Why don't you sit down?

23
00:03:06.523 --> 00:03:09.120
It's nice and quiet in here. isn't it?

24
00:03:09.294 --> 00:03:11.697
Quiet. soothing. calm.

25
00:03:14.837 --> 00:03:16.568
Calm.

26
00:03:23.251 --> 00:03:25.153
I've been watching you
and your husband...

27
00:03:25.321 --> 00:03:29.420
and I want you to know that I understand
what you're feeling right now.

28
00:03:31.966 --> 00:03:34.494
You have no idea.

29
00:03:35.906 --> 00:03:36.931
Believe me.

30
00:03:37.576 --> 00:03:40.879
I do. I know.

31
00:03:41.449 --> 00:03:45.082
- I know. and I wanna help you.
- You can't help me.

32
00:03:46.124 --> 00:03:50.064
- What do you know?
- All sorts of things.

33
00:03:51.166 --> 00:03:55.231
- You really only pretend to like skiing. right?
- Yes. but...

34
00:03:55.406 --> 00:03:58.139
You're pleased that your best friend
recently gained some weight.

35
00:03:58.312 --> 00:04:02.217
About 10 pounds. You wish you'd been
more adventurous when you were younger.

36
00:04:02.386 --> 00:04:05.722
You love India. but you've never
been there. You have trouble sleeping.

37
00:04:05.892 --> 00:04:08.227
Your favorite color...

38
00:04:09.431 --> 00:04:11.264
is blue.

39
00:04:12.136 --> 00:04:15.575
I don't understand. You're...?

40
00:04:15.942 --> 00:04:18.709
- You're psychic?
- Ha. no.

41
00:04:19.548 --> 00:04:20.642
Just paying attention.

42
00:04:22.020 --> 00:04:25.117
I used to make a good living
pretending to be a psychic.

43
00:04:26.460 --> 00:04:29.193
I tell you this
because I want you to understand...

44
00:04:29.365 --> 00:04:31.700
there's no point hiding things from me.

45
00:04:34.574 --> 00:04:36.670
Hiding what?

46
00:04:36.845 --> 00:04:39.646
You know what I see
when I look at your husband?

47
00:04:40.651 --> 00:04:44.250
I see a warm. loving. generous man.

48
00:04:44.425 --> 00:04:49.333
A little vain. maybe. Selfish. Controlling.
But a decent man.

49
00:04:49.500 --> 00:04:51.026
Yes.

50
00:04:54.041 --> 00:04:57.276
So why do you suspect him
of murdering your daughter?

51
00:05:01.087 --> 00:05:02.751
I don't.

52
00:05:04.493 --> 00:05:08.263
- The McCluskey boy did it.
- Yes. that's what the police say.

53
00:05:09.267 --> 00:05:12.205
But you think they're wrong. Why?

54
00:05:12.974 --> 00:05:16.709
I don't know. I don't know. I...

55
00:05:17.148 --> 00:05:19.015
Tell me.

56
00:05:19.586 --> 00:05:24.186
The last year.
they have been so strange with each other.

57
00:05:24.360 --> 00:05:28.494
And neither one would admit that
anything was wrong. And I think that...

58
00:05:30.405 --> 00:05:34.675
I think that she tried to tell me once.
and I didn't... I...

59
00:05:36.782 --> 00:05:40.119
God. Oh. God.

60
00:05:40.488 --> 00:05:42.151
Did you ask him if he killed her?

61
00:05:44.162 --> 00:05:45.495
What would he say?

62
00:05:45.664 --> 00:05:48.693
Most wives can tell
when their husbands are lying.

63
00:05:50.505 --> 00:05:53.306
Yes. Yes.

64
00:05:54.012 --> 00:05:57.782
I... I don't want... Uh...
The McCluskey boy did it.

65
00:05:57.952 --> 00:05:59.148
Maybe.

66
00:06:04.397 --> 00:06:06.629
You think he did it too?

67
00:06:07.535 --> 00:06:09.266
I trust a mother's instinct.

68
00:06:12.110 --> 00:06:13.511
June?

69
00:06:15.148 --> 00:06:16.640
There you are.

70
00:06:17.919 --> 00:06:19.651
Hi. Who are you?

71
00:06:20.691 --> 00:06:23.185
I'm the police.
Did you kill your daughter?

72
00:06:28.638 --> 00:06:30.073
How dare you?

73
00:06:30.241 --> 00:06:33.237
I asked you a simple question. sir.
Did you kill your daughter?

74
00:06:34.949 --> 00:06:38.410
- No. I did not kill my daughter.
- Oh.

75
00:06:38.588 --> 00:06:42.050
Now. you get the hell out of my house.

76
00:06:43.030 --> 00:06:44.499
June?

77
00:06:45.167 --> 00:06:47.434
June. what's the matter with you?

78
00:06:49.541 --> 00:06:50.908
I'm gonna have your badge.

79
00:06:51.077 --> 00:06:53.604
An innocent man
would've punched me by now.

80
00:06:53.782 --> 00:06:56.048
I am gonna make life miserable for you.

81
00:06:56.219 --> 00:06:59.681
You come in here. you accost my wife.
You cause trouble. uh...

82
00:07:01.695 --> 00:07:03.187
June.

83
00:07:04.734 --> 00:07:06.431
June. honey. please...

84
00:07:06.604 --> 00:07:08.437
Shots fired. Inside.

85
00:07:08.607 --> 00:07:10.237
Move. move!

86
00:07:10.411 --> 00:07:11.971
Hey.

87
00:07:15.887 --> 00:07:17.720
Honestly. it's not as bad as it looks.

88
00:07:21.763 --> 00:07:25.498
Mrs. Tolliver? Mrs. Tolliver? Please wait.

89
00:07:26.304 --> 00:07:28.138
Front room's clear.

90
00:07:50.213 --> 00:07:52.342
Then the son of a bitch eagles 17.

91
00:07:52.516 --> 00:07:55.078
Are you kidding me? On that course?

92
00:07:55.522 --> 00:07:57.287
A damn eagle?

93
00:07:57.458 --> 00:08:01.057
That course never suited you. Price.
We'll do better in Orlando.

94
00:08:01.232 --> 00:08:04.227
- We have a nice spot on the draw.
- Well. I'll tell you what.

95
00:08:04.404 --> 00:08:07.570
Davis Love III can kiss my butt.

96
00:08:18.428 --> 00:08:21.833
Alison? Alison?

97
00:08:34.055 --> 00:08:36.116
<i>Flight 233 from Sacramento...</i>

98
00:08:36.292 --> 00:08:39.663
<i>you may claim your baggage
from Carousel 2.</i>

99
00:08:39.832 --> 00:08:41.893
<i>Flight 233 from Sacramento...</i>

100
00:08:42.069 --> 00:08:44.198
Uh. sorry.

101
00:08:44.639 --> 00:08:46.974
You checked luggage?
What are you. on vacation?

102
00:08:47.144 --> 00:08:49.666
- No. ma'am. Won't do it again.
- When your trousseau arrives...

103
00:08:49.715 --> 00:08:52.619
pick up the second rental
and go to the sheriff's department.

104
00:08:52.787 --> 00:08:55.452
Hustle us up a couple of rooms.
furniture and phone lines.

105
00:08:55.625 --> 00:08:57.152
Yes. ma'am.

106
00:08:57.329 --> 00:08:59.026
Come on. let's go.

107
00:09:08.148 --> 00:09:09.981
Morning. everybody.

108
00:09:10.151 --> 00:09:13.385
- How was your flight?
- Go away. You're on suspension.

109
00:09:14.291 --> 00:09:15.851
Thank you.

110
00:09:16.729 --> 00:09:20.635
- Mandated leave. Ends next week.
- So come back next week.

111
00:09:20.803 --> 00:09:24.003
- Hot enough for you?
- Which one of you jackasses told him?

112
00:09:24.175 --> 00:09:25.701
- It was you. wasn't it. Cho?
- Yes.

113
00:09:25.878 --> 00:09:29.248
Of course he called me. It's Red John.
Can't keep me out of this.

114
00:09:29.417 --> 00:09:30.442
Why would you want to?

115
00:09:30.619 --> 00:09:32.589
You got a man killed.
There's consequences.

116
00:09:32.757 --> 00:09:36.093
A man that murdered his daughter
because she wouldn't have sex with him?

117
00:09:36.262 --> 00:09:38.893
You did not know that.
If she hadn't left the diary...

118
00:09:39.067 --> 00:09:42.233
But she did. though. Be reasonable.
This is my case.

119
00:09:42.407 --> 00:09:44.673
- Your case?
- Red John's mine.

120
00:09:44.844 --> 00:09:46.747
Red John doesn't belong to anyone.

121
00:09:49.886 --> 00:09:50.911
He belongs to me.

122
00:09:52.457 --> 00:09:56.795
It's not my call. Rules are rules.
Come back next week.

123
00:09:57.933 --> 00:10:00.131
Don't let this man past.

124
00:10:06.815 --> 00:10:08.284
Boss.

125
00:10:08.452 --> 00:10:12.586
We have Gregory Tannen.
Caucasian. male. 43. single.

126
00:10:12.759 --> 00:10:14.388
We haven't opened him up yet. but...

127
00:10:14.562 --> 00:10:18.661
Sorry I went over your head.
I'll redeem myself. I promise.

128
00:10:18.836 --> 00:10:20.465
You want redemption. be silent.

129
00:10:20.639 --> 00:10:22.872
- Okay. I can learn to do that.
- Shh.

130
00:10:24.980 --> 00:10:26.004
Sorry.

131
00:10:28.819 --> 00:10:32.589
Burn marks here indicate that
the victim was subdued with a stun gun...

132
00:10:32.760 --> 00:10:34.856
standard civilian model.
by the look of it.

133
00:10:35.031 --> 00:10:38.299
Death appears to be caused by
several blows to the back of the skull...

134
00:10:38.469 --> 00:10:41.567
consistent with the bloody golf club
found at the scene.

135
00:10:41.742 --> 00:10:46.912
Female is Alison Randolph.
27. married. no children.

136
00:10:47.085 --> 00:10:50.855
They were found at her listed residence.
TOD looks to be early Saturday evening.

137
00:10:51.025 --> 00:10:52.688
On Alison. we have stun-gun marks...

138
00:10:52.861 --> 00:10:55.958
followed by binding
with tight. black. plastic ligatures...

139
00:10:56.133 --> 00:10:59.834
frenzied cutting and stabbing assault
of the torso. and abuse of the viscera.

140
00:11:00.007 --> 00:11:01.944
- Textbook Red John.
- Who found the bodies?

141
00:11:02.111 --> 00:11:05.208
This one's husband. coming home
from the airport with his brother.

142
00:11:05.383 --> 00:11:06.909
- He's a pro golfer.
- Oh. yeah?

143
00:11:07.086 --> 00:11:08.487
Price Randolph?

144
00:11:08.655 --> 00:11:12.254
- What's her deal with him? Do we know?
- He's on file as one of her physicians.

145
00:11:12.428 --> 00:11:14.091
- Making a house call?
- Lovers?

146
00:11:14.265 --> 00:11:16.201
No. This one's gay.

147
00:11:18.840 --> 00:11:21.437
Dr. Wagner might know
what their relationship was.

148
00:11:21.611 --> 00:11:23.103
He's here to make the formal ID.

149
00:11:25.151 --> 00:11:26.745
Okay.

150
00:11:27.388 --> 00:11:30.793
Dr. Wagner. Hi.

151
00:11:30.961 --> 00:11:34.559
I'm Agent Teresa Lisbon.
California Bureau of Investigation.

152
00:11:34.734 --> 00:11:37.797
- What's your connection to the victims?
- Well. I work with Gregory.

153
00:11:37.973 --> 00:11:42.311
Dr. Tannen and the Randolph family
are long-time clients of our practice.

154
00:11:42.480 --> 00:11:45.247
- Are house calls the norm at your practice?
- No.

155
00:11:45.419 --> 00:11:47.481
Gregory and Alison were close friends.

156
00:11:47.656 --> 00:11:50.059
- Lovers?
- No. He was gay.

157
00:11:50.695 --> 00:11:52.632
No. they were just friends.

158
00:11:53.666 --> 00:11:56.638
- What in God's name happened to them?
- Looks like Red John.

159
00:11:58.642 --> 00:12:01.239
- Who's Red John?
- We don't know who did this.

160
00:12:02.348 --> 00:12:05.445
We'll be in touch probably. Thank you.

161
00:12:11.363 --> 00:12:12.662
Tracy wanna set up? Here?

162
00:12:12.833 --> 00:12:13.858
Yeah. that's good.

163
00:12:14.035 --> 00:12:16.302
Red John enters here.

164
00:12:16.473 --> 00:12:18.534
Excuse me. Sorry.

165
00:12:18.710 --> 00:12:20.475
He comes around here.

166
00:12:21.314 --> 00:12:25.483
He waits for her.
expecting her to come in alone.

167
00:12:25.655 --> 00:12:28.125
Only thing. her friend Tannen
chose the wrong night...

168
00:12:28.293 --> 00:12:31.026
to come over for a Richard Gere
and ice-cream orgy.

169
00:12:32.334 --> 00:12:36.502
So Red John zaps them both
with his trusty stun gun...

170
00:12:36.674 --> 00:12:38.871
and... Excuse me.

171
00:12:39.044 --> 00:12:40.947
Grabs a five iron from the bag here...

172
00:12:41.115 --> 00:12:43.882
and... Ugh!

173
00:12:46.458 --> 00:12:47.859
Crushes Tannen's skull.

174
00:12:48.762 --> 00:12:52.360
Then he takes his sweet time
dealing with Alison how he likes.

175
00:12:52.835 --> 00:12:53.997
She's a nice big girl...

176
00:12:54.171 --> 00:12:57.872
so unless he's pretty strong. I'm
guessing that he grabbed her by the arms...

177
00:12:58.044 --> 00:13:00.038
and dragged her down the hall.

178
00:13:43.824 --> 00:13:45.020
Deeply sorry.

179
00:13:46.462 --> 00:13:48.955
He asks you to forgive him.

180
00:13:49.734 --> 00:13:51.294
Can you do that Jenny?

181
00:13:53.207 --> 00:13:55.439
- He needs to hear it.
- I forgive you. Daddy.

182
00:13:55.610 --> 00:13:57.979
- Oh. yes.
- I forgive you.

183
00:13:58.482 --> 00:13:59.712
He's smiling now.

184
00:14:01.153 --> 00:14:02.486
There are tears of joy.

185
00:14:04.793 --> 00:14:06.957
He says. "God bless you and keep you."

186
00:14:13.041 --> 00:14:14.066
He's gone.

187
00:14:25.762 --> 00:14:30.100
- Amazing. amazing. Amazing.
- She's amazed.

188
00:14:32.374 --> 00:14:34.003
- Patrick...
- One second.

189
00:14:34.177 --> 00:14:37.673
- Give him some time.
- Abso... Come on back to us.

190
00:14:37.850 --> 00:14:39.946
- I'm back. Thank you.
- He's back. Ha-ha-ha.

191
00:14:40.121 --> 00:14:45.860
So. Patrick. I understand that
you're also sort of a paranormal detective.

192
00:14:46.031 --> 00:14:49.368
- Is that right?
- I try to help the police when I can.

193
00:14:49.838 --> 00:14:54.040
And you're helping them hunt
this scary serial killer.

194
00:14:54.212 --> 00:14:56.182
- What's his name? Red John.
- Red John.

195
00:14:56.349 --> 00:15:01.188
There she blows.
Classic Red John smiley face.

196
00:15:01.357 --> 00:15:07.893
Drawn in the victims' blood. clockwise.
with three fingers of his right hand...

197
00:15:08.069 --> 00:15:10.097
wearing a rubber kitchen glove.

198
00:15:10.540 --> 00:15:14.001
- I'm stoked to finally see one in the flesh.
- This isn't Red John.

199
00:15:15.482 --> 00:15:16.506
Right.

200
00:15:17.585 --> 00:15:20.284
Red John thinks of himself
as a showman. an artist.

201
00:15:20.457 --> 00:15:23.258
He has a strong sense of theater.
In the previous killings...

202
00:15:23.429 --> 00:15:26.094
he made sure that the first thing
that anyone sees...

203
00:15:26.267 --> 00:15:28.329
is the face on the wall.

204
00:15:28.504 --> 00:15:30.737
You see the face first. and you know.

205
00:15:30.909 --> 00:15:33.471
You know what's happened.
and you feel dread.

206
00:15:33.647 --> 00:15:36.380
Then. and only then.
do you see the body of the victim.

207
00:15:36.552 --> 00:15:38.021
Always in that order.

208
00:15:38.188 --> 00:15:42.390
Here. it's the opposite.
The first thing you see is the body...

209
00:15:42.562 --> 00:15:45.865
and you have to look around
to see the face on the wall.

210
00:15:46.535 --> 00:15:50.441
- Doesn't play nearly as well. does it?
- Depends on your taste. I suppose.

211
00:15:50.609 --> 00:15:54.549
No. Come on. The killer could've painted
on the correct wall here. but he didn't...

212
00:15:54.716 --> 00:15:57.483
because he didn't know better.
because he isn't Red John.

213
00:15:58.156 --> 00:16:01.925
Wow. That's interesting.

214
00:16:03.732 --> 00:16:06.169
You know what your problem is.
my friend?

215
00:16:06.337 --> 00:16:09.036
You enjoy your work a little too much.
You're a ghoul.

216
00:16:10.611 --> 00:16:13.378
If you don't get horny reading <i>Fangoria.</i>
I'm Britney Spears.

217
00:16:13.549 --> 00:16:15.382
I... I resent that.

218
00:16:15.552 --> 00:16:19.185
- This is you trying to redeem yourself. is it?
- I'm sorry.

219
00:16:19.927 --> 00:16:21.692
He irks me.

220
00:16:22.063 --> 00:16:23.191
He's irksome.

221
00:16:25.269 --> 00:16:26.363
You don't need me here.

222
00:16:41.630 --> 00:16:45.866
- So. yeah. this one doesn't fit the pattern.
- So Jane was right. We have a copycat.

223
00:16:46.039 --> 00:16:49.739
Or we have Red John trying new things.
Or we have Red John making a mistake.

224
00:16:49.911 --> 00:16:52.712
We don't know.
We'll work the evidence until we do know.

225
00:16:53.851 --> 00:16:56.345
- Go talk to the husband.
- Will do. boss.

226
00:17:01.365 --> 00:17:03.392
What are you waiting for?

227
00:17:24.405 --> 00:17:28.037
Hey. So you might be right
about this case. Might be.

228
00:17:28.211 --> 00:17:30.148
Thanks for the insight.

229
00:17:30.782 --> 00:17:32.810
No. Did I say that?

230
00:17:32.986 --> 00:17:36.356
I'm acknowledging the fact
that you might be right. that's all.

231
00:17:36.525 --> 00:17:40.090
I mean. if you wanted to come back.
I couldn't stop you.

232
00:17:41.167 --> 00:17:44.606
Yeah. fine. I'm asking you to come back.

233
00:17:46.310 --> 00:17:47.870
Because.

234
00:17:48.046 --> 00:17:51.018
Because you're useful to the team.

235
00:17:51.819 --> 00:17:54.346
No. No. I won't say "please."
Go screw yourself.

236
00:17:55.658 --> 00:17:57.356
Jackass.

237
00:18:06.711 --> 00:18:08.181
Good morning.

238
00:18:08.348 --> 00:18:10.011
Can I help you?

239
00:18:11.386 --> 00:18:13.151
You must be Van Pelt.

240
00:18:13.322 --> 00:18:14.814
Pleasure. Patrick Jane.

241
00:18:14.992 --> 00:18:17.793
Oh. hi. Good to meet you.
Agent Cho said you'd left town.

242
00:18:18.231 --> 00:18:19.700
No. Nowhere to go.

243
00:18:21.269 --> 00:18:22.602
Okay. Um.

244
00:18:22.772 --> 00:18:25.642
Do you want that desk over there.
or this one?

245
00:18:25.810 --> 00:18:29.807
- I mean. that one gets more light.
- That one. More light. by all means.

246
00:18:32.322 --> 00:18:34.884
Very pleasant addition
to the Serious Crimes family.

247
00:18:35.060 --> 00:18:37.258
Oh. Hi. When did you get here?

248
00:18:38.232 --> 00:18:39.759
<i>Stop. I give up.</i>

249
00:18:39.935 --> 00:18:42.098
<i>Aah! Stop. Stop. Turn off the camera.</i>

250
00:18:42.272 --> 00:18:44.074
<i>Tag. Come on. come on. come on.</i>

251
00:18:44.209 --> 00:18:46.651
<i>- Okay. we're done. We're done.
- Stop. Good. good.</i>

252
00:18:47.681 --> 00:18:49.447
<i>You are awful.</i>

253
00:18:50.286 --> 00:18:52.416
<i>- Go. go. go.
- Stop. please.</i>

254
00:18:52.857 --> 00:18:54.725
<i>Stop.</i>

255
00:18:58.133 --> 00:19:01.629
I lost a beautiful. precious angel.

256
00:19:02.874 --> 00:19:04.435
Yes. sir.

257
00:19:04.611 --> 00:19:05.635
Good-looking woman.

258
00:19:09.786 --> 00:19:11.628
I'm jumping right in.
if you don't mind. Price.

259
00:19:11.790 --> 00:19:13.817
You missed the tournament cut
on Friday. yes?

260
00:19:13.994 --> 00:19:17.763
But you didn't come home until Sunday.
What'd you do with the rest of your time?

261
00:19:17.934 --> 00:19:20.269
I get this.
You guys can't catch the real killer...

262
00:19:20.438 --> 00:19:22.534
- so you wanna lay this one on me?
- No. sir.

263
00:19:22.709 --> 00:19:27.173
If we have confirmation of where you were.
lets us exclude you from the investigation.

264
00:19:36.900 --> 00:19:39.633
I was with a massage therapist.

265
00:19:39.805 --> 00:19:41.172
Name?

266
00:19:42.409 --> 00:19:48.285
- Uh. it had "lady" in there somewhere.
- It'll be on his credit-card bill.

267
00:19:48.754 --> 00:19:50.280
There you go.

268
00:19:50.457 --> 00:19:52.519
Pleasure meeting you. boys.

269
00:19:55.132 --> 00:19:58.070
We're a full-service private practice.

270
00:19:58.738 --> 00:20:02.701
We deliver primary care.
uh. cosmetic surgery...

271
00:20:02.878 --> 00:20:05.645
psychotherapy. sports medicine.
you name it.

272
00:20:05.816 --> 00:20:07.308
What's the African connection?

273
00:20:07.787 --> 00:20:09.586
It's what this place is all about.

274
00:20:09.757 --> 00:20:12.695
Half our profits go to build
and staff basic health clinics...

275
00:20:12.863 --> 00:20:14.696
in poor African communities.

276
00:20:15.868 --> 00:20:17.235
All right. here we are.

277
00:20:19.674 --> 00:20:20.938
It's a thin file.

278
00:20:22.045 --> 00:20:24.949
Alison was a healthy young woman.

279
00:20:25.116 --> 00:20:28.385
- Psychiatric history?
- She didn't have one.

280
00:20:28.556 --> 00:20:30.389
STDs? Abortions?

281
00:20:30.559 --> 00:20:33.053
- Unexplained injuries?
- No.

282
00:20:33.230 --> 00:20:37.136
Aside from some routine checkups with me.
it's all Dr. Tannen. all aesthetic work.

283
00:20:37.304 --> 00:20:38.773
Did Tannen keep a diary?

284
00:20:39.175 --> 00:20:42.841
Our last case was solved
because the victim kept a diary.

285
00:20:43.015 --> 00:20:44.712
Diary? I don't think so.

286
00:20:44.884 --> 00:20:46.786
Getting back to Alison Randolph.

287
00:20:47.823 --> 00:20:50.226
How was her marriage. do you think?

288
00:20:50.394 --> 00:20:51.988
Happy? Unhappy?

289
00:20:52.999 --> 00:20:56.597
About six months ago.
Dr. Tannen asked my advice.

290
00:20:58.174 --> 00:21:02.079
Alison asked him to get her a year's supply
of birth-control pills. off the books...

291
00:21:02.248 --> 00:21:04.445
which is strictly against AMA code.

292
00:21:05.153 --> 00:21:07.818
I said. "Sure. do it."

293
00:21:08.992 --> 00:21:13.957
- Better us than some Tijuana drugstore.
- Why the secrecy?

294
00:21:14.903 --> 00:21:19.401
Price Randolph had a vasectomy.
April of '02.

295
00:21:20.146 --> 00:21:24.280
- If there's anything else I can do...
- I appreciate that.

296
00:21:25.522 --> 00:21:28.722
Actually. there is.
Uh. I'm out of sleeping pills.

297
00:21:30.196 --> 00:21:32.531
Can you fix me up?
Anything strong will do.

298
00:21:32.701 --> 00:21:36.401
Sure. Come in for a consultation.
We'll squeeze you in this afternoon.

299
00:21:36.574 --> 00:21:40.138
Oh. no. I was hoping to get something now.
Trying to avoid the chitchat.

300
00:21:42.217 --> 00:21:47.524
I'm sorry. I wouldn't feel comfortable
prescribing without some sort of chitchat.

301
00:21:50.865 --> 00:21:52.232
I'll call you.

302
00:21:52.401 --> 00:21:53.836
Maybe.

303
00:21:56.208 --> 00:21:57.409
I like the husband for it.

304
00:21:57.577 --> 00:22:01.711
He hires some hooker to create an alibi.
flies home. fillets the spouse. flies back.

305
00:22:01.884 --> 00:22:05.289
It's a classic. elaborate and clever.
but ultimately stupid plan.

306
00:22:05.457 --> 00:22:07.290
Have you looked
at his PGA tournament record?

307
00:22:07.460 --> 00:22:10.057
It's not bad. Six mil career earnings.

308
00:22:10.232 --> 00:22:14.172
For coming in second and third. Put him on
the 18th tee with a big one on the line...

309
00:22:14.339 --> 00:22:16.367
like night follows day. he'll shank it.

310
00:22:16.543 --> 00:22:19.947
He's a choker. He doesn't have the nerve
to kill his wife. Didn't do it.

311
00:22:20.923 --> 00:22:24.593
Are you suggesting we drop a prime suspect
because he's never won a major?

312
00:22:24.760 --> 00:22:28.138
Oh. no. no. no.
I'm just making idle conversation.

313
00:22:29.348 --> 00:22:30.599
How'd you do that?

314
00:22:32.268 --> 00:22:34.103
Telekinesis.

315
00:22:34.270 --> 00:22:35.729
He blew on it.

316
00:22:37.579 --> 00:22:39.573
That is another way to do it.

317
00:22:41.186 --> 00:22:45.456
Mr. Jane. I have a question
regarding your previous career path.

318
00:22:45.626 --> 00:22:47.061
Fire away.

319
00:22:47.229 --> 00:22:50.167
When you met with other psychics.
real psychics...

320
00:22:50.334 --> 00:22:52.805
could they tell
you were just pretending?

321
00:22:52.972 --> 00:22:54.966
There's no such thing as real psychics.

322
00:22:55.143 --> 00:22:58.013
I beg to differ.
My cousin Yolanda's a psychic.

323
00:22:58.181 --> 00:23:00.652
Your cousin is deluded or dishonest.
or both.

324
00:23:00.819 --> 00:23:04.554
- Hey. steady.
- No. He's entitled to his opinion.

325
00:23:04.726 --> 00:23:06.127
He's wrong. though.

326
00:23:06.295 --> 00:23:07.821
- She has power.
- Thank you.

327
00:23:07.998 --> 00:23:11.233
She can communicate with the other side.
I've seen her do it myself.

328
00:23:11.404 --> 00:23:13.807
She let you speak
with someone that's gone?

329
00:23:13.976 --> 00:23:15.343
- Yes.
- Someone you love...

330
00:23:15.511 --> 00:23:18.847
- and still miss very much?
- Yes.

331
00:23:19.017 --> 00:23:21.511
You wanted her power to be real.
so it was.

332
00:23:22.557 --> 00:23:23.582
No.

333
00:23:23.759 --> 00:23:26.424
You're sure you're right.
Science don't know everything.

334
00:23:26.597 --> 00:23:29.228
Five hundred years ago.
radio would've seemed like magic.

335
00:23:29.402 --> 00:23:31.873
- Exactly.
- In the future. it could be totally normal...

336
00:23:32.040 --> 00:23:34.322
- to communicate with the other side.
- The other side?

337
00:23:34.378 --> 00:23:35.938
Mm-hm.

338
00:23:38.618 --> 00:23:40.918
Your father's a football coach. yeah?

339
00:23:41.657 --> 00:23:44.561
- How'd you know that?
- It's obvious from your whole demeanor.

340
00:23:44.728 --> 00:23:48.691
My point is. didn't Dad
always say life is like football?

341
00:23:48.869 --> 00:23:51.534
When that final whistle blows.
the game is over.

342
00:23:52.174 --> 00:23:55.705
Done. There is no more.
There is no other side.

343
00:23:55.881 --> 00:23:59.753
This is it. Lobster and bread rolls
and nautical kitsch. and then...

344
00:23:59.921 --> 00:24:01.550
pfft. nothingness.

345
00:24:02.592 --> 00:24:06.896
You poor. sad man.
The Kingdom of God is a real place.

346
00:24:08.135 --> 00:24:11.905
Okay. later tonight. when Rigsby asks you
to come back to his hotel room...

347
00:24:16.616 --> 00:24:17.778
say yes.

348
00:24:17.952 --> 00:24:18.977
Excuse me?

349
00:24:19.154 --> 00:24:22.149
I know. you were planning on
refusing him very curtly.

350
00:24:22.326 --> 00:24:26.495
First week on the job. you wanna set
a tone. no monkey business. But why not?

351
00:24:26.668 --> 00:24:29.333
Rigsby's an excellent lover. I'm sure.

352
00:24:29.506 --> 00:24:32.376
Tough. but fair. Right?

353
00:24:32.544 --> 00:24:33.843
Right.

354
00:24:39.189 --> 00:24:41.318
The Kingdom of God is a real place.
Mr. Jane.

355
00:24:42.695 --> 00:24:45.496
And you have an immortal soul.

356
00:24:45.667 --> 00:24:48.571
Oh. I do so hope you're wrong.

357
00:24:54.416 --> 00:24:55.441
- Good night.
- Night.

358
00:24:55.618 --> 00:24:57.520
Later. dude.

359
00:25:04.733 --> 00:25:06.795
This is me.

360
00:25:11.011 --> 00:25:15.851
- Welcome to the unit. Agent Van Pelt.
- Thank you. Agent Rigsby.

361
00:25:16.520 --> 00:25:18.753
<i>She explodes into action.</i>

362
00:25:18.925 --> 00:25:22.625
<i>Reaching up to 60 miles per hour...</i>

363
00:25:22.798 --> 00:25:26.795
<i>she easily outruns her terrified prey.</i>

364
00:26:19.196 --> 00:26:21.895
"Greetings. old friend. It's been a while.

365
00:26:22.067 --> 00:26:25.164
I hope you are keeping well.
I am thriving and happy.

366
00:26:25.339 --> 00:26:28.540
I have 12 wives now
and will soon begin courting Number 13.

367
00:26:29.646 --> 00:26:31.115
Why can't you catch me?

368
00:26:31.283 --> 00:26:35.052
You must feel so powerless
and stupid and sad.

369
00:26:35.223 --> 00:26:37.057
Oh. well. All the best.

370
00:26:38.262 --> 00:26:40.061
Red John."

371
00:26:40.232 --> 00:26:42.226
That sounds like the real deal to me.

372
00:26:42.402 --> 00:26:46.239
Sounds like Red John. It's not. Red John
wouldn't risk capture just to taunt me.

373
00:26:46.409 --> 00:26:48.675
So the real killer's trying
to throw us off track?

374
00:26:48.846 --> 00:26:51.613
Cho. find out where Price Randolph was
a half an hour ago.

375
00:26:51.785 --> 00:26:55.280
Rigsby. check the hotel security cameras.
Get those over to Forensics.

376
00:27:01.702 --> 00:27:04.367
- You okay?
- Absolutely.

377
00:27:05.041 --> 00:27:06.704
Get some sleep.

378
00:27:44.743 --> 00:27:45.768
Hello.

379
00:27:45.945 --> 00:27:48.382
- Good morning.
- You didn't sleep. did you?

380
00:27:53.459 --> 00:27:56.898
Hi. I'd like to make an appointment
with Dr. Wagner. please. It's urgent.

381
00:27:57.064 --> 00:27:59.058
Jane. Patrick Jane.

382
00:27:59.235 --> 00:28:01.228
Yeah. I'll hold.

383
00:28:01.405 --> 00:28:02.738
Forensics maybe got a break.

384
00:28:03.309 --> 00:28:05.871
Blood on the cloth in the envelope
is Alison Randolph's.

385
00:28:06.047 --> 00:28:10.044
But they found a hair in there.
doesn't belong to her or Tannen.

386
00:28:10.588 --> 00:28:12.148
Guess who it does belong to.

387
00:28:13.659 --> 00:28:15.391
It's yours. Tag. Amazing. huh?

388
00:28:20.138 --> 00:28:21.232
Science.

389
00:28:26.416 --> 00:28:29.081
This is insane. I didn't...

390
00:28:29.254 --> 00:28:30.775
<i>I didn't kill Alison.</i>

391
00:28:30.923 --> 00:28:32.859
<i>How do you explain your hair?</i>

392
00:28:33.026 --> 00:28:36.898
<i>Either it was a mistake.
or I'm being framed.</i>

393
00:28:37.066 --> 00:28:38.296
<i>Who would wanna frame you?</i>

394
00:28:38.469 --> 00:28:40.391
<i>We don't want to.
if that's what you're thinking.</i>

395
00:28:40.540 --> 00:28:42.373
He and Alison were lovers.

396
00:28:42.543 --> 00:28:44.137
<i>Who would wanna frame you. Tag?</i>

397
00:28:46.216 --> 00:28:49.120
<i>- My brother.
- Why would he wanna do that?</i>

398
00:28:51.592 --> 00:28:53.027
<i>Alison and I were lovers.</i>

399
00:28:54.931 --> 00:28:57.767
I think you are psychic.
You're just afraid to admit it.

400
00:28:57.937 --> 00:28:59.406
Mm-hm.

401
00:29:00.675 --> 00:29:02.508
So...

402
00:29:06.050 --> 00:29:07.577
So. heh.

403
00:29:10.658 --> 00:29:12.093
Why is it you can't sleep?

404
00:29:12.261 --> 00:29:15.928
Because I can't get the good pills
without talking to a doctor.

405
00:29:17.337 --> 00:29:19.330
- And you don't like talking to doctors.
- Eh.

406
00:29:19.507 --> 00:29:22.742
They always wanna be the smartest person
in the room. don't they?

407
00:29:22.913 --> 00:29:25.247
When. in fact. that's me. obviously.

408
00:29:29.357 --> 00:29:33.024
You protect your core self very fiercely.

409
00:29:34.199 --> 00:29:36.670
What do you think is the reason for that?

410
00:29:38.806 --> 00:29:41.437
You know.
this is exactly how I imagined it would be.

411
00:29:42.980 --> 00:29:44.974
You gonna ask me about my mother?

412
00:29:45.151 --> 00:29:48.453
- Do you want me to ask about your mother?
- I just wanna sleep.

413
00:29:49.892 --> 00:29:52.261
So. what is it that keeps you awake?

414
00:29:53.966 --> 00:29:55.937
Oh. what's his name? Red John?

415
00:29:56.103 --> 00:30:01.478
That's right. Red John. Uh. he's killed
at least eight women that we know of.

416
00:30:01.646 --> 00:30:04.015
Uh. the police asked me
to get a psychic fix on him...

417
00:30:04.184 --> 00:30:06.154
to get a sense of who this man is.

418
00:30:06.321 --> 00:30:10.489
How do you do that exactly?
Get a psychic fix on someone.

419
00:30:11.129 --> 00:30:14.329
Well. Davis.
true demonic evil burns like fire.

420
00:30:14.501 --> 00:30:18.305
It burns with a terrible. cold. dark flame.

421
00:30:18.475 --> 00:30:21.470
<i>I force myself to look into that flame...</i>

422
00:30:21.648 --> 00:30:26.351
<i>and I see an image of the evildoer.
In this case. Red John.</i>

423
00:30:27.124 --> 00:30:31.462
<i>He's an ugly. tormented little man.
A lonely soul.</i>

424
00:30:31.632 --> 00:30:35.162
<i>Sad. Very sad.</i>

425
00:30:55.439 --> 00:30:56.669
<i>"Dear Mr. Jane.</i>

426
00:30:56.841 --> 00:30:58.709
<i>I do not like to be slandered
in the media...</i>

427
00:30:58.879 --> 00:31:00.974
<i>especially by a dirty.
moneygrubbing fraud.</i>

428
00:31:01.149 --> 00:31:02.482
<i>If you were a real psychic...</i>

429
00:31:02.652 --> 00:31:06.147
<i>instead of a dishonest little worm.
you wouldn't need to open the door...</i>

430
00:31:06.324 --> 00:31:09.957
<i>to see what I've done
to your lovely wife and child."</i>

431
00:31:18.913 --> 00:31:20.075
<i>Mr. Jane.</i>

432
00:31:21.017 --> 00:31:22.953
Mr. Jane?

433
00:31:24.089 --> 00:31:26.617
What is it that keeps you awake?

434
00:31:28.429 --> 00:31:29.989
Um...

435
00:31:35.108 --> 00:31:38.570
You know. when I was a boy.
we had a farm.

436
00:31:38.748 --> 00:31:40.775
There was a lot of work.

437
00:31:42.788 --> 00:31:46.283
- I was kind of a lazy kid.
- Yes?

438
00:31:50.534 --> 00:31:54.805
I'd always be trying to get my little
brother. Jimmy. to do my chores for me.

439
00:31:57.012 --> 00:32:00.975
One day. I promised him a dollar
if he'd cut the firewood.

440
00:32:01.153 --> 00:32:03.886
- Heh.
- Well...

441
00:32:04.793 --> 00:32:08.961
he opened up an artery in his leg
on the saw. and he bled to death.

442
00:32:11.371 --> 00:32:13.068
Died...

443
00:32:14.876 --> 00:32:16.140
doing my chores for me.

444
00:32:22.723 --> 00:32:24.625
You know...

445
00:32:24.793 --> 00:32:29.895
that's almost exactly the same thing
that happened to Johnny Cash.

446
00:32:30.069 --> 00:32:31.663
Is it really?

447
00:32:33.209 --> 00:32:34.940
Wow.

448
00:32:35.913 --> 00:32:37.280
That's spooky.

449
00:32:42.657 --> 00:32:44.904
- Mr. Randolph...
- Cut the crap. My brother's done nothing.

450
00:32:44.928 --> 00:32:47.991
You haven't got the stones to come
after me so you come after my family.

451
00:32:48.168 --> 00:32:50.331
- That is flat-out persecution.
- What did we agree?

452
00:32:50.504 --> 00:32:54.205
Mr. Randolph. there's no intent to persecute
you. We are holding your brother...

453
00:32:54.378 --> 00:32:57.874
because we have evidence linking him
to the crime. and potential motive.

454
00:32:58.051 --> 00:33:01.114
Whenever you weren't around. he was
banging your wife like a big bass drum.

455
00:33:02.826 --> 00:33:04.956
Tag and Alison?

456
00:33:07.801 --> 00:33:10.466
That's what he states.
He states that you killed Alison.

457
00:33:10.640 --> 00:33:13.168
- You're trying to frame him in revenge.
- What did you say?

458
00:33:13.344 --> 00:33:15.211
What...? There... Bastard.

459
00:33:15.381 --> 00:33:17.716
- Hey.
- You... Ow! Agh!

460
00:33:17.885 --> 00:33:20.186
- Son of a bitch.
- You treated her like crap.

461
00:33:20.356 --> 00:33:21.381
What'd you expect?

462
00:33:21.558 --> 00:33:24.894
I didn't expect my little brother
to be banging my wife. you bastard!

463
00:33:34.815 --> 00:33:37.582
Everything you told me is total fiction.
isn't it?

464
00:33:39.389 --> 00:33:41.018
Yes.

465
00:33:41.392 --> 00:33:42.918
Why?

466
00:33:43.096 --> 00:33:46.091
I can tell you're in real pain.
Why not tell the truth?

467
00:33:47.737 --> 00:33:49.297
The truth is mine.

468
00:33:53.246 --> 00:33:55.239
- I hear you.
- Thank you.

469
00:34:02.896 --> 00:34:05.458
Oh. yes.

470
00:34:06.436 --> 00:34:08.838
Remember. uh. we were talking
about Tannen the other day?

471
00:34:09.007 --> 00:34:11.410
I asked you if he kept a diary.
and you said he did.

472
00:34:11.578 --> 00:34:13.845
- Well. there's no diary among his effects.
- No.

473
00:34:14.016 --> 00:34:15.076
I'm sorry. no?

474
00:34:15.685 --> 00:34:18.954
No. You have it wrong.
I didn't think he kept a diary.

475
00:34:19.125 --> 00:34:21.027
Strange.

476
00:34:21.462 --> 00:34:24.127
Then it must've been someone else
who told me.

477
00:34:24.300 --> 00:34:25.963
Either that. or I'm going mad.

478
00:34:27.906 --> 00:34:32.005
But I definitely. 100 percent.
remember hearing that Tannen kept a diary.

479
00:34:32.180 --> 00:34:35.449
Well. that is strange.
But why does it matter if he kept a diary?

480
00:34:35.620 --> 00:34:36.953
You're right. doesn't matter.

481
00:34:37.122 --> 00:34:41.187
Only. I was thinking. why do magicians
have beautiful girl assistants?

482
00:34:42.465 --> 00:34:45.699
- Why?
- They're reliable distractors of attention.

483
00:34:45.870 --> 00:34:48.398
People will look at a beautiful girl
for a long time...

484
00:34:48.575 --> 00:34:50.910
before they look
where they should be looking...

485
00:34:51.080 --> 00:34:53.881
if they wanna see
how the trick really works.

486
00:34:55.120 --> 00:34:57.557
I'll send over
a couple of Forensics guys tomorrow...

487
00:34:57.724 --> 00:34:59.922
to search his office
and locate that diary.

488
00:35:00.096 --> 00:35:02.590
Didn't they already search his office?

489
00:35:02.767 --> 00:35:05.033
Oh. they never do it thoroughly
the first time.

490
00:35:05.204 --> 00:35:06.366
Once more for luck. yeah?

491
00:35:07.374 --> 00:35:10.574
Gotta be there somewhere.
Thanks for everything. doc.

492
00:35:10.747 --> 00:35:13.115
Good night. Good night.

493
00:35:50.148 --> 00:35:52.016
Lost something?

494
00:35:53.454 --> 00:35:55.583
- How did you get in?
- Door was open.

495
00:35:55.758 --> 00:35:59.163
- I think I left my phone in your office.
- The door wasn't open.

496
00:35:59.331 --> 00:36:01.495
Must've been. Here I am.

497
00:36:07.011 --> 00:36:08.810
What are you doing?

498
00:36:11.819 --> 00:36:17.729
I confess. the temptation to play detective
was a little too strong.

499
00:36:18.164 --> 00:36:20.658
I was looking for that diary.

500
00:36:22.438 --> 00:36:25.205
- I got a little carried away.
- No kidding.

501
00:36:26.545 --> 00:36:28.276
But no diary?

502
00:36:28.882 --> 00:36:30.408
No diary.

503
00:36:32.054 --> 00:36:35.049
Maybe I should have a gander.
I'm good at finding things.

504
00:36:36.061 --> 00:36:37.553
Be my guest.

505
00:37:41.273 --> 00:37:42.298
Eureka.

506
00:37:47.985 --> 00:37:49.785
Dr. Wagner. thanks for your help.

507
00:37:59.472 --> 00:38:01.101
Mr. Jane...

508
00:38:01.275 --> 00:38:04.406
uh. your phone.

509
00:38:04.580 --> 00:38:06.244
Right. Ha.

510
00:38:08.020 --> 00:38:09.785
Thanks.

511
00:38:17.002 --> 00:38:19.166
Yeah. got it.

512
00:38:19.339 --> 00:38:22.938
- Silly of me. Well. goodbye again.
- Wait.

513
00:38:26.151 --> 00:38:28.384
Give me the diary.

514
00:38:50.760 --> 00:38:52.924
- That's very amusing.
- I try.

515
00:38:58.006 --> 00:39:02.140
I knew...
I knew it might be a trick. but I...

516
00:39:03.716 --> 00:39:07.953
- I had to be sure.
- Yes. That's how the trick works.

517
00:39:09.192 --> 00:39:10.422
What led you to me?

518
00:39:11.429 --> 00:39:14.026
Not that I'm saying I did it.
I'm just asking.

519
00:39:14.601 --> 00:39:17.402
When we first met. you said
you didn't know who Red John was.

520
00:39:17.574 --> 00:39:22.949
But you have books on criminal psychiatry
there that have chapters on him.

521
00:39:23.551 --> 00:39:25.214
You're the Randolph family doctor...

522
00:39:25.387 --> 00:39:28.690
so you could easily get
a strand of Tag's hair.

523
00:39:28.860 --> 00:39:31.525
And. being a doctor...

524
00:39:32.265 --> 00:39:35.705
you can hack up another human
without difficulty.

525
00:39:36.941 --> 00:39:38.843
It's obvious it was you.

526
00:39:40.246 --> 00:39:42.149
That's it?

527
00:39:42.717 --> 00:39:44.812
You have nothing.

528
00:39:44.988 --> 00:39:47.721
- That's just guesswork.
- Oh. I know.

529
00:39:47.893 --> 00:39:50.660
I just wanted to be sure
I had the right answer.

530
00:39:52.667 --> 00:39:58.235
I was surprised. I gotta be honest.
You don't seem to be a wicked man.

531
00:39:59.446 --> 00:40:00.574
But you are.

532
00:40:03.753 --> 00:40:06.281
You're angry about the letter.

533
00:40:07.426 --> 00:40:10.296
Yeah. it was a bit mean-spirited.

534
00:40:12.001 --> 00:40:14.438
For the record.
I'm sorry about your family.

535
00:40:15.207 --> 00:40:21.082
I can only imagine your pain.
But I'm not a wicked man.

536
00:40:21.484 --> 00:40:24.320
- My conscience is clear.
- Really?

537
00:40:24.723 --> 00:40:28.993
Right now in Africa. there's 3000
beautiful children alive today...

538
00:40:29.164 --> 00:40:32.934
who should be dead. but they aren't.
because of me.

539
00:40:33.938 --> 00:40:39.712
Tannen was gonna ruin me
and destroy all that work...

540
00:40:41.986 --> 00:40:44.423
over nothing. Money.

541
00:40:45.024 --> 00:40:48.088
Theft. he called it.

542
00:40:48.264 --> 00:40:52.363
Embezzlement. Self-righteous idiot.

543
00:40:53.473 --> 00:41:00.385
It's simple math. If I go to
jail. thousands of kids will die.

544
00:41:00.552 --> 00:41:06.518
So I made a rational. moral decision
to kill Tannen for the greater good.

545
00:41:06.695 --> 00:41:09.496
And Alison? What'd she do wrong?

546
00:41:10.469 --> 00:41:11.494
Mm.

547
00:41:11.904 --> 00:41:15.901
As we said. she was the magician's
assistant. just a distraction.

548
00:41:16.078 --> 00:41:17.945
- Ah.
- If only Tannen died...

549
00:41:18.116 --> 00:41:21.054
the police would've
been all over this place. wouldn't they?

550
00:41:21.621 --> 00:41:25.425
Truly. is killing two
any worse than killing one...

551
00:41:25.595 --> 00:41:28.465
when so many lives are at stake?
I don't think so.

552
00:41:29.168 --> 00:41:31.570
You poor. sad man.

553
00:41:31.738 --> 00:41:35.200
- You're under arrest. Let's go.
- I'm pointing a gun at you.

554
00:41:35.378 --> 00:41:40.184
You really think I would set you up so
nicely and let you pull a loaded gun on me?

555
00:41:40.954 --> 00:41:43.084
I took the bullets out earlier.

556
00:41:57.249 --> 00:42:00.119
- You're late. Draw your weapon.
- What? Huh?

557
00:42:00.722 --> 00:42:01.952
Drop the gun.

558
00:42:02.392 --> 00:42:05.421
Hands on your head.
Get down on your knees.

559
00:42:05.597 --> 00:42:07.396
Down.

560
00:42:23.328 --> 00:42:24.854
Closed-case doughnuts are here.

561
00:42:35.616 --> 00:42:38.782
I just went to get sleeping pills. I swear.
I didn't even wanna go.

562
00:42:38.955 --> 00:42:41.221
- You know I didn't wanna go.
- Right.

563
00:42:42.527 --> 00:42:44.691
Yeah. you didn't set Wagner up.

564
00:42:45.532 --> 00:42:47.298
Didn't figure it was him days ago.

565
00:42:47.470 --> 00:42:49.804
You didn't let us tear apart
the victim's family...

566
00:42:49.974 --> 00:42:51.967
to satisfy your childish need for drama.

567
00:42:52.144 --> 00:42:55.207
Hey. that family was screwed anyway.
Don't blame yourselves. guys.

568
00:43:14.850 --> 00:43:17.845
Don't even start. I'm still angry.

569
00:43:18.256 --> 00:43:20.523
- I'm sorry.
- No. you're not.

570
00:43:27.605 --> 00:43:32.308
A frog? Well.
this makes everything better. doesn't it?
